God bless America.

04:43.783 --> 04:45.702
Robert Urich!

04:45.785 --> 04:46.869
{\an1}Wasn't Bart Braverman
in this show?

04:46.953 --> 04:49.372
Bart Braverman!

04:49.455 --> 04:52.041
{\an5}DAVID:
<i>Well, there's always</i>
<i>a bright side.</i>

04:52.125 --> 04:54.210
{\an3}At least they didn't
stick us with the, uh...

04:54.293 --> 04:56.045
Charlie Manson Band
for our next video.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.380
Don't joke about this.

04:57.463 --> 04:58.715
I am freaking out here.

04:58.798 --> 05:00.383
I cannot work with Ray.

05:00.466 --> 05:02.552
Donna, we have to at least have
this meeting, all right?

05:02.635 --> 05:03.553
We owe

05:03.636 --> 05:04.679
{\an3}that much
to Erik.

05:04.762 --> 05:06.723
Well, what am I supposed
to say to Ray?

05:06.806 --> 05:08.766
Donna, relax, all right?

05:08.850 --> 05:10.560
It's over between you and Ray.

05:10.643 --> 05:12.770
Besides, he's not going to want
to do this video with us

05:12.854 --> 05:14.856
{\an3}any more than we want
to do it with him.

05:14.939 --> 05:18.192
I mean, if Joe finds out about
this, he is going to flip out.

05:18.276 --> 05:20.069
You know what?
It's none of my business,

05:20.153 --> 05:22.155
but I don't think
you should say anything to Joe.

05:22.238 --> 05:24.365
Donna, we're gonna have

05:24.449 --> 05:26.242
this meeting, then the
whole thing is going to be over.

05:26.325 --> 05:28.369
You think so?

05:28.453 --> 05:29.370
{\an3}Yes.

05:29.454 --> 05:32.206
Why cause any more problems?

05:32.290 --> 05:34.709
Fine.

05:34.792 --> 05:35.877
You're right.

05:35.960 --> 05:37.170
I won't tell Joe.

05:43.301 --> 05:45.219
JOE:
<i>Tell me the truth.</i>

05:45.303 --> 05:46.346
You're doing fine.

05:46.429 --> 05:48.765
{\an3}All the equipment's working
just the way it should.

05:48.848 --> 05:50.475
Here, see for yourself.

05:50.558 --> 05:53.269
{\an1}Yeah, like I know what
(chuckles)g at.

05:53.352 --> 05:57.065
Yeah, well, you go and
you have a great life.

05:57.148 --> 05:58.441
Sure. thank you.

05:58.524 --> 05:59.776
Sure.s for everything.

05:59.859 --> 06:00.568
Just don't forget.

06:00.651 --> 06:02.904
Reserve my Rose
Bowl seats now.

06:02.987 --> 06:04.197
(chuckles)

06:04.280 --> 06:06.074
{\an3}Actually, Dr. Martin,
I don't know

06:06.157 --> 06:07.992
{\an3}if I'll be playing
football next season.

06:08.076 --> 06:09.660
Why not?
Your health is fine.

06:09.744 --> 06:11.079
You don't have
to give up football.

06:11.162 --> 06:12.789
Oh, I'm not going to give it up.

06:12.872 --> 06:14.373
I'm just not going to play.

06:14.457 --> 06:17.168
{\an3}I'm gonna go back home
and coach high school ball.

06:17.251 --> 06:18.377
Pennsylvania?

06:18.461 --> 06:20.004
{\an3}That's right, Beaver
Falls High School.

06:20.088 --> 06:21.589
That's where my dad
used to coach.

06:21.672 --> 06:23.007
Both my brother and I
played there.

06:23.091 --> 06:24.175
They lost the coach

06:24.258 --> 06:26.552
and they asked me to come out
and help for the summer.

06:26.636 --> 06:28.096
Oh, well, it's just
for the summer then?

06:28.179 --> 06:29.972
No.

06:30.056 --> 06:32.809
In the fall, I'm gonna take over
the program full-time.

06:37.230 --> 06:39.148
Does Donna know this?

06:39.232 --> 06:40.983
Not yet.

06:41.067 --> 06:42.860
She's going to be heartbroken
that you're leaving.

06:42.944 --> 06:44.570
She cares a lot about you.

06:46.155 --> 06:50.326
And I care a lot about her.

06:50.409 --> 06:51.911
So can I ask you a favor?

06:51.994 --> 06:54.288
Yeah, sure.

06:55.248 --> 06:57.375
Don't say anything to Donna,

06:57.458 --> 06:59.377
just for a while.

06:59.460 --> 07:01.671
{\an3}When do you plan
on talking to her?

07:01.754 --> 07:05.174
I don't know.

07:05.258 --> 07:06.843
Soon.

07:14.350 --> 07:17.186
{\an3}I don't know how to
break this to you, Kel,

07:17.270 --> 07:18.855
{\an3}but if that's your
homework, it's late.

07:18.938 --> 07:19.856
School's out.

07:19.939 --> 07:21.023
No, not for me.

07:21.107 --> 07:22.483
I have a lot to make up.

07:22.567 --> 07:23.484
Summer semester, huh?

07:23.568 --> 07:25.361
If I'm lucky.

07:25.444 --> 07:27.196
Hey, Nat, uh,
can you come next door?

07:27.280 --> 07:28.364
The bondsman's waiting.

07:28.447 --> 07:30.533
{\an1}Ugh, that guy gives me
the creeps.

07:30.616 --> 07:31.701
He's all right.

07:31.784 --> 07:32.618
He's a snake.

07:32.702 --> 07:34.495
Well, then you ought
to get along with him

07:34.579 --> 07:37.039
just fine, Valerie.

07:37.123 --> 07:39.167
{\an1}It's nice to see you,
too, Kel.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.544
Enjoy school.

07:41.627 --> 07:44.338
Thanks. I will.

07:48.301 --> 07:50.219
Mr. Carr.

07:50.303 --> 07:52.013
{\an3}Ms. Malone.

07:52.096 --> 07:54.056
{\an1}This is my partner
Nat Bussichio.

07:54.140 --> 07:58.227
Well, any partner of Val's
is a partner of mine,

07:58.311 --> 08:00.897
{\an3}technically
speaking.

08:00.980 --> 08:03.566
{\an1}Can I get you a cup of coffee
or a beer or something?

08:03.649 --> 08:06.068
{\an3}No, thanks.

08:06.152 --> 08:09.447
{\an1}Technically speaking, where
exactly do we stand here?

08:09.530 --> 08:11.365
{\an3}Luckily, we still
have some time.

08:11.449 --> 08:12.575
180 days to be exact.

08:12.658 --> 08:13.576
Cut to the chase.

08:13.659 --> 08:15.369
Where does that leave us?

08:15.453 --> 08:16.412
Well, according

08:16.495 --> 08:19.707
to your partnership papers,
your equity helped

08:19.790 --> 08:22.251
{\an3}to secure the money
necessary to build this club.

08:22.335 --> 08:23.920
{\an3}Therefore, I have
the legal right

08:24.003 --> 08:25.254
{\an3}to attach you
to any debt

08:25.338 --> 08:27.423
{\an3}I'm trying to recover
from Ms. Malone.

08:27.506 --> 08:29.759
That is, of course, if
Colin doesn't return.

08:29.842 --> 08:31.427
I'm sorry, Nat.

08:31.510 --> 08:34.472
It's okay.

08:34.554 --> 08:36.890
Couldn't we hire someone
to find Robbins,

08:36.974 --> 08:39.602
like a, a bounty hunter
or a detective?

08:39.684 --> 08:42.020
They usually take
25% of the bond,

08:42.104 --> 08:44.565
{\an3}and that cost would have
to be underwritten entirely

08:44.649 --> 08:45.816
{\an3}by you.

08:45.900 --> 08:48.069
That's $25,000.

08:48.152 --> 08:51.280
{\an3}Well, there's always one last
option I tell my clients.

08:51.364 --> 08:52.281
What's that?

08:52.365 --> 08:53.407
{\an3}Put the
prisoner's picture

08:53.491 --> 08:56.285
on a milk carton
and hope we get lucky.

08:57.328 --> 08:59.372
(quietly):
He's a snake.

09:05.044 --> 09:07.964
I love Las Vegas.

09:08.047 --> 09:10.341
(both laughing)

09:10.424 --> 09:12.260
Great, great show.

09:12.343 --> 09:13.261
Great writers.

09:13.344 --> 09:15.054
{\an1}Yeah, great writers,
great writers.

09:15.137 --> 09:17.181
{\an1}I-I never would have thought
that the hooker...

09:17.265 --> 09:18.432
{\an1}...was fixing
the roulette wheel

09:18.516 --> 09:19.642
{\an1}to pay
for her mother's operation.

09:19.725 --> 09:20.977
What a heart.gs)

09:21.060 --> 09:23.521
{\an1}Heart, heart,
the girl had heart.

09:23.604 --> 09:26.190
Don't get up.

