worried about Colin.

26:15.573 --> 26:17.575
Have you heard from him?

26:18.576 --> 26:20.495
Uh... Colin.

26:20.578 --> 26:22.163
Yeah, yeah, he's-he's gone.

26:22.247 --> 26:25.166
I know I hurt him, but I can't
let him go without me.

26:25.250 --> 26:27.002
He's my whole world.

26:27.085 --> 26:28.670
I really love him.

26:28.753 --> 26:30.171
You really mean that, don't you?

26:31.923 --> 26:33.174
Here.

26:33.258 --> 26:34.676
{\an3}Come sit.

26:34.759 --> 26:36.803
{\an3}So, you think
he's still in L.A.?

26:38.763 --> 26:40.515
{\an1}I don't know why
I'm gonna tell you this.

26:40.598 --> 26:42.183
I'm gonna tell you though.

26:42.267 --> 26:43.685
Yeah, he's still in L.A.

26:43.768 --> 26:45.854
{\an1}I don't know where,
but, uh,

26:45.937 --> 26:47.939
he's got a beeper.

26:50.025 --> 26:51.318
I'll give you the number.

26:51.401 --> 26:53.403
Great.

26:56.448 --> 26:58.450
Oh, thank you.

27:00.535 --> 27:02.162
So, what can I get you?

27:02.245 --> 27:03.705
I can go by weight.

27:03.788 --> 27:05.206
Um, just a gram.

27:05.290 --> 27:06.833
Gram, you Yeah.

27:06.916 --> 27:08.168
That's not much.

27:08.251 --> 27:10.462
{\an3}I gotta tell you,
this stuff is primo.

27:10.545 --> 27:12.881
Why don't you have a taste
with me?

27:12.964 --> 27:14.716
No, actually, I have to go.

27:14.799 --> 27:16.384
I-I'm meeting my mom somewhere.

27:16.468 --> 27:18.178
All the better.

27:19.262 --> 27:21.181
Maybe some other time, huh?

27:21.264 --> 27:23.058
I'll just take that gram
for now.

27:30.065 --> 27:32.525
{\an1}All right.

27:33.526 --> 27:35.111
That's it. I'm going in.

27:35.195 --> 27:37.238
Don't leave me here.

27:43.370 --> 27:45.288
I know how to find him.

27:45.372 --> 27:46.706
{\an1}Great. Let's get
out of here.

27:46.790 --> 27:48.208
{\an3}Did you buy
anything?

27:48.291 --> 27:49.376
Yeah, I had to.

27:49.459 --> 27:50.543
Give it to me.

27:50.627 --> 27:52.045
Brandon,
I'll take care of it.

27:52.128 --> 27:54.130
Give it to me.

28:14.943 --> 28:16.152
{\an3}Donna?

28:16.236 --> 28:18.154
{\an3}What are you doing
sittin' in the dark?

28:18.238 --> 28:20.281
Just sittin'.

28:21.241 --> 28:23.284
Are you okay?

28:24.536 --> 28:26.454
I don't know.

28:26.538 --> 28:28.748
What's wrong?

28:32.794 --> 28:35.338
Joe, uh...

28:35.422 --> 28:37.340
Joe decided to move back East.

28:37.424 --> 28:40.301
And he wants me
to go with him.

28:40.385 --> 28:42.345
He asked me to marry him.

28:42.429 --> 28:45.223
What?

28:45.306 --> 28:46.683
{\an3}Oh, my...

28:46.766 --> 28:49.310
wha... what-what did you say?

28:49.394 --> 28:51.980
I didn't say anything.

28:52.063 --> 28:53.982
Wow.

28:54.065 --> 28:56.317
Beaver Falls sounds
beautiful and all,

28:56.401 --> 28:58.153
but let's face it,

28:58.236 --> 29:00.155
I'm an L.A. girl.

29:00.238 --> 29:01.990
Do you love him?

29:02.073 --> 29:03.324
Yeah.

29:03.408 --> 29:04.826
{\an3}Well, then

29:04.909 --> 29:06.494
what's there to think about?

29:06.578 --> 29:09.581
Joe wants me to change
my whole life.

29:10.582 --> 29:12.167
I just...

29:12.250 --> 29:14.294
I don't know if I can do that.

29:17.755 --> 29:19.674
Well, when does he want
an answer?

29:19.757 --> 29:21.468
He wants to know right away.

29:23.428 --> 29:25.847
Well, if you want, I can stay up
with you tonight, you know.

29:25.930 --> 29:27.515
No.

29:27.599 --> 29:29.517
Thanks, but, um,

29:29.601 --> 29:30.935
you go to bed.

29:31.936 --> 29:34.022
Okay.

29:34.105 --> 29:36.107
Night.

29:38.943 --> 29:40.862
You know I've been

29:40.945 --> 29:42.906
{\an3}having my own brush
with destiny.

29:42.989 --> 29:44.824
{\an3}I've been
thinking

29:44.908 --> 29:47.243
a lot about my mom lately.

29:47.327 --> 29:50.330
You know, what kind of dreams
she might have had for me.

29:50.413 --> 29:53.041
{\an3}Being with Carl again
brings that

29:53.124 --> 29:55.877
all up.

29:55.960 --> 29:57.921
He really loved my mom,
you know.

29:58.004 --> 30:01.257
It must be nice to have someone
to share that with again.

30:01.341 --> 30:02.509
{\an3}It is.

30:02.592 --> 30:05.512
Carl keeps, um,

30:05.595 --> 30:08.598
bringing up the old memories.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.519
He told me that, uh,

30:12.602 --> 30:14.521
my mom told him

30:14.604 --> 30:17.106
she wanted us to have
a royal wedding one day.

30:17.190 --> 30:19.108
Wow.

30:19.192 --> 30:22.028
She really did have big dreams
for you, didn't she?

30:22.111 --> 30:25.031
Yeah.

30:25.114 --> 30:27.700
It's funny 'cause
later that night

30:27.784 --> 30:30.370
when she was putting me to bed,
she told me the same thing,

30:30.453 --> 30:32.372
{\an3}only Carl
doesn't know.

30:32.455 --> 30:34.290
Are you gonna tell hNo.

30:34.374 --> 30:37.126
I don't want him
to get the wrong idea.

30:38.628 --> 30:40.838
So, you sure you're okay?

30:40.922 --> 30:42.799
Yeah.

30:42.882 --> 30:45.051
Would you, uh, just turn out
the light though?

30:45.134 --> 30:47.470
Yeah.

30:48.888 --> 30:51.224
Don?

30:51.307 --> 30:52.809
Yeah.

30:52.892 --> 30:56.062
Remember when you
were a little girl

30:56.145 --> 30:58.565
and you used to fantasize
about your wedding day?

30:59.524 --> 31:01.859
Of course.

31:01.943 --> 31:03.820
Every little girl does.

31:03.903 --> 31:06.447
Those fantasies are all

31:06.531 --> 31:09.158
becoming a little too real,
aren't they?

31:11.202 --> 31:13.621
They sure are.

31:15.582 --> 31:17.000
Good night.

31:17.083 --> 31:18.960
Night.

31:34.559 --> 31:36.811
{\an3}Why don't you try
and page him again?

31:36.894 --> 31:38.813
I've already paged him
three times, Brandon.

31:38.896 --> 31:40.189
Maybe he doesn't know it's you.

31:40.273 --> 31:41.983
{\an4}KELLY:
Valerie, I think
he's called my car phone

31:42.066 --> 31:43.818
{\an1}enough to know
that it's my number.

31:43.901 --> 31:45.486
{\an3}Oh, that's right.
He's in love with you.

31:45.570 --> 31:46.487
I, I forgot.

31:46.571 --> 31:47.822
{\an3}BRANDON:
Guys,

31:47.905 --> 31:49.824
he's probably not even
in L.A. anymore, okay?

31:49.907 --> 31:50.950
{\an1}KELLY:
What if he is?

31:51.034 --> 31:52.994
{\an1}What exactly do you
plan on doing?

31:53.077 --> 31:55.163
Are you gonna ask him to
politely turn himself in,

31:55.246 --> 31:57.332
or are you just gonna
charge right in there,

31:57.415 --> 31:58.499
take care of things?

31:58.583 --> 31:59.667
I'm not afraid of Colin.

31:59.751 --> 32:01.502
BRANDON:
Oh,Ladies,am?

32:01.586 --> 32:04.505
we're on the same side
on this, okay?

32:04.589 --> 32:06.299
If he calls,
I say we set up the meeting,

32:06.382 --> 32:08.343
then we call the police
and let them do their job.

32:08.426 --> 32:10.011
You know, it's late.

32:10.094 --> 32:12.055
{\an3}Maybe he just turned the
beeper off and went to sleep.

32:12.138 --> 32:13.848
Yeah, maybe we should
call it a night

32:13.931 --> 32:15.058
and try this again
tomorrow, huh?

32:15.141 --> 32:16.184
(cell phone ringing)

32:19.812 --> 32:20.730
{\an3}Well,
answer it.

32:20.813 --> 32:21.856
Okay.

32:21.939 --> 32:23.399
(beep)

32:23.483 --> 32:24.859
Hello.

32:24.942 --> 32:26.861
Kelly, it's me.

32:26.944 --> 32:27.862
Colin,

32:27.945 --> 32:29.030
{\an1}I'm so glad
you called back.

32:29.113 --> 32:30.365
{\an1}I've been paging you
all night.

32:30.448 --> 32:32.241
You alone?

32:32.325 --> 32:33.868
Yeah, yeah.

32:33.951 --> 32:35.328
Um, where are you?

32:35.411 --> 32:36.329
Are you okay?

32:36.412 --> 32:37.163
Yeah, I'm fine.

32:37.246 --> 32:39.374
I've had to do
a lot of moving around.

32:39.457 --> 32:42.043
{\an1}Look, I, um,
I have to see you.

32:42.126 --> 32:43.878
I don't know, Kelly.

32:43.961 --> 32:45.213
It's-it's not safe.

32:45.296 --> 32:47.548
Please.

32:53.930 --> 32:55.932
All right.

32:56.015 --> 32:57.225
But not tonight.

32:57.308 --> 32:58.351
Look, I'll call you
tomorrow, okay?

32:58.434 --> 32:59.352
Yeah.

32:59.435 --> 33:00.561
I love you, Kelly.

33:00.645 --> 33:01.854
I need you.

33:01.938 --> 33:03.356
I need you now more than ever.

33:03.439 --> 33:07.026
I need you, too, Colin.

33:07.110 --> 33:09.195
Bye.

33:09.278 --> 33:10.279
(beep)

33:25.086 --> 33:26.087
Hey, Donna.

33:26.170 --> 33:27.255
{\an3}Hi, Wendy.

33:27.338 --> 33:28.631
{\an3}You guys
loading out?

33:28.715 --> 33:31.050
{\an1}Yeah, we have a show in,
uh, San Luis Obispo tonight.

33:31.134 --> 33:33.344
Oh, don't think I got
a chance to tell you,

33:33.428 --> 33:34.595
but the show was
great last night.

33:34.679 --> 33:35.763
{\an3}And I love
the new song.

33:35.847 --> 33:37.348
You know, he wrote that
for you, Donna?

33:37.432 --> 33:40.476
Yeah, I was, I was wondering
about that.

33:40.560 --> 33:41.769
{\an3}WENDY:
Hey, Donna,

33:41.853 --> 33:43.104
thanks for being so nice to us.

33:43.187 --> 33:44.981
It was really great meeting you.
You made this

33:45.064 --> 33:46.232
a real special homecoming
for Ray.

33:46.315 --> 33:47.233
{\an6}DONNA:
Well, we're
all real happy

33:47.316 --> 33:48.943
Thanks. guys.

33:49.026 --> 33:50.903
Uh, I'm gonna go see what's left
in the dressing room.

33:50.987 --> 33:51.779
{\an3}Okay.

33:51.863 --> 33:53.239
See you lOkay.

33:56.868 --> 33:58.411
{\an3}Wendy,
Wendy's great.

33:58.494 --> 34:00.997
Yeah, I know, she is.

34:01.080 --> 34:02.957
{\an1}Look, I owe you
a lot, Donna.

34:03.040 --> 34:05.042
Well, let's just make
a great video together

34:05.126 --> 34:06.961
and call it even.
(chuckles)

34:07.044 --> 34:07.795
You got a deal.

34:07.879 --> 34:10.465
I just hope
you're as happy as I am.

34:10.547 --> 34:12.550
Nobody deserves it
more than you do.

34:12.632 --> 34:14.510
{\an1}I hope you have
all the happiness

34:14.594 --> 34:16.012
{\an1}in the world,
Donna, I mean that.

34:16.094 --> 34:18.473
Especially after
what I did to you.

34:18.556 --> 34:21.809
Thanks.

34:21.893 --> 34:25.103
I, uh, I really needed
to hear that right now.

34:31.444 --> 34:32.987
(phone ringing)

34:33.070 --> 34:34.112
Hello.

34:34.197 --> 34:35.447
It's me.

34:35.531 --> 34:37.449
I'm at the Palm Court Motel.

34:37.533 --> 34:38.784
It's, uh, it's in Reseda.

34:38.868 --> 34:40.203
I'm in room 106.

34:40.286 --> 34:41.661
I'll be waiting for you here.

34:41.746 --> 34:43.748
Hang on, hang on,
let me write it...

34:47.918 --> 34:49.629
Okay, the Palm Court,

34:49.712 --> 34:50.713
106.

34:50.797 --> 34:53.007
Yeah. Look, how long
will it take you to get here?

34:53.090 --> 34:54.717
Uh, a few hours.

34:54.801 --> 34:55.967
Is there a problem?

34:56.052 --> 34:57.220
Yeah. Just come right now.

34:57.303 --> 35:00.306
I can't, Colin, I have a-a few
things I have to finish up here.

35:00.389 --> 35:01.516
Like what?

35:01.599 --> 35:03.351
Uh, I-I have
a doctor's appointment.

35:03.434 --> 35:04.811
I'll be there as soon as I can.

35:04.894 --> 35:06.020
Just hurry.

35:06.103 --> 35:07.021
I will.

35:07.105 --> 35:08.022
Kelly.

35:08.105 --> 35:10.483
What?

35:10.566 --> 35:11.526
Can I trust you?

35:11.609 --> 35:13.653
Of course you can.

35:13.736 --> 35:14.821
See you soon.

35:22.245 --> 35:25.164
{\an1}And to show my gratitude
to the two of you

35:25.248 --> 35:26.916
{\an1}for bearing with me
through my mumbling time,

35:26.999 --> 35:29.168
I'd like
to pay for lunch.

35:29.252 --> 35:31.838
{\an1}I thought I heard the familiar
sound of gums flapping!

35:31.921 --> 35:33.339
Yeah, they're mine.

35:33.422 --> 35:35.550
{\an3}Do me a favor: set us up
with three mega burgers, okay?

35:35.633 --> 35:36.551
You got it, pal.

35:36.634 --> 35:37.844
Thanks.

35:37.927 --> 35:39.846
Okay, let's give
those lips a try.

35:39.929 --> 35:41.305
{\an1}STEVE:
Yeah, that's wise?

35:41.389 --> 35:42.515
the kisser's still
a little sore.

35:42.598 --> 35:43.724
{\an3}I'll be the
judge of that.

35:43.808 --> 35:45.101
Okay.

35:45.184 --> 35:46.102
Mmm.

35:46.185 --> 35:47.270
{\an3}Is that where
it hurts?

35:47.353 --> 35:49.105
{\an1}Yeah, but I think
we're back in business.

35:54.694 --> 35:56.237
KELLY:
<i>I hate this.</i>

35:56.320 --> 35:57.405
I feel like such a snitch.

35:57.488 --> 36:00.116
Come on, Kel, it's not like
the guy cheated on a test.

36:00.199 --> 36:01.534
{\an3}I thought you didn't care
about him anyway.

36:01.617 --> 36:03.411
I don't, but still.

36:03.494 --> 36:04.620
Here we go.

36:05.663 --> 36:06.622
DANNY:
Hey!

36:06.706 --> 36:07.957
{\an6}RENDELL:
We'd like to
talk to you.

36:08.040 --> 36:09.458
Hey, lock my door.

36:09.542 --> 36:10.751
{\an3}Wait, that's
not Colin.

36:10.835 --> 36:11.919
{\an1}RENDELL:
Take it easy now.

36:12.003 --> 36:12.962
You have the right

36:13.045 --> 36:14.422
to speak to an attorney.

36:14.505 --> 36:16.549
DANNY:
I don't need to hear my rights.

36:16.632 --> 36:17.550
What'd I do?

36:17.633 --> 36:19.051
{\an4}RENDELL:
What were you doing
in that room, huh?

36:19.135 --> 36:20.428
I'm staying here.

36:20.511 --> 36:21.429
Check the register.

36:21.512 --> 36:24.265
Danny Fivinsky, all right?

36:24.348 --> 36:25.224
If you don't let go of me,

36:25.308 --> 36:26.809
you're gonna have a lawsuit
on your hands.

36:26.893 --> 36:28.102
I want you to know that.

36:28.185 --> 36:29.437
Where's Colin?

36:29.520 --> 36:30.438
Who's Colin?

36:30.521 --> 36:31.564
What are you talking about?

36:32.690 --> 36:33.941
Who are these people?

36:34.025 --> 36:35.443
YKELLY:w
thiYes.y?

36:35.526 --> 36:36.736
{\an3}He-he's a
drug dealer.

36:36.819 --> 36:38.404
{\an3}That's how I got
Colin's beeper number.

36:38.487 --> 36:40.990
{\an1}I never seen this girl
before in my life.

36:41.073 --> 36:43.284
{\an6}RENDELL:
You're coming
with us, pal.

36:43.367 --> 36:44.952
Fine, no problem.

36:45.036 --> 36:46.829
I got nothing to hide.

36:49.040 --> 36:51.042
Colin knew.

36:51.125 --> 36:52.501
He saw right through me.

36:52.585 --> 36:53.961
Danny told him
and set us up.

36:54.045 --> 36:55.922
{\an3}Now, you can bet if
Danny was in that motel room,

36:56.005 --> 36:57.298
Colin ain't far off.

36:57.381 --> 36:59.300
{\an1}Well, maybe the police
will have some luck

36:59.383 --> 37:00.635
{\an1}when they put
the pressure on him.

37:00.718 --> 37:02.303
No way.

37:02.386 --> 37:03.804
He knew we had nothing on him.

37:03.888 --> 37:06.766
This was our one chance,
and we blew it.

37:06.849 --> 37:08.309
What did you say
to Colin anyways?

37:08.392 --> 37:10.269
You cVal, she did been
tooher best.ng.

37:10.353 --> 37:11.771
I don't need you
to defend me, Brandon.

37:11.854 --> 37:13.689
Let's go.

37:23.783 --> 37:26.327
{\an1}I didn't get much sleep
last night.

37:26.410 --> 37:28.496
No, neither did I.

37:28.579 --> 37:32.166
The one thing...

37:32.250 --> 37:35.378
that I know for sure...

37:35.461 --> 37:38.839
is how much I love you.

37:38.923 --> 37:40.925
And I love you, too.

37:44.387 --> 37:46.055
But there's a
"but" coming.

37:51.102 --> 37:54.563
I'm just not ready yet.

37:54.647 --> 37:56.440
I mean, we're both so young.

37:56.524 --> 38:00.027
My mother was 19
when she got married.

38:00.111 --> 38:02.363
Yeah.

38:02.446 --> 38:04.573
My mom was young, too.

38:07.326 --> 38:09.245
She got pregnant.

38:09.328 --> 38:11.372
She...

38:11.455 --> 38:15.084
She had to get married.

38:15.167 --> 38:17.795
She lost the baby.

38:17.878 --> 38:20.881
{\an1}And even though her and my dad
worked things out...

38:23.426 --> 38:25.177
I know she still wonders

38:25.261 --> 38:26.846
{\an1}what she could have done
with her life.

38:26.929 --> 38:28.723
It wouldn't be that way with us.

38:29.765 --> 38:31.726
Maybe not.

38:34.979 --> 38:37.231
But I...

38:37.315 --> 38:39.025
I'm not ready
to leave my friends,

38:39.108 --> 38:40.609
say good-bye

38:40.693 --> 38:42.737
to my family...

38:45.364 --> 38:48.743
give up the few years of freedom

38:48.826 --> 38:51.245
we all have left
before we have to grow up.

38:51.328 --> 38:53.122
{\an1}I mean,
I still have

38:53.205 --> 38:56.125
so many dreams
that I haven't even tried

38:56.208 --> 38:58.252
to make come true yet.

39:00.880 --> 39:04.258
And I don't want to go with you

39:04.341 --> 39:06.927
and wonder what my life
might have been like.

39:07.011 --> 39:09.096
{\an1}You'd wind up
hating me.

39:11.057 --> 39:13.225
Can you understand that?

39:18.522 --> 39:19.607
Yeah.

39:24.570 --> 39:26.614
I still wish I could
change your mind.

39:28.574 --> 39:31.243
Well, maybe I can change yours.

39:31.327 --> 39:32.787
{\an1}I mean,

39:32.870 --> 39:39.001
if I asked you to stay here,
here with me, would you?

39:45.382 --> 39:47.426
Uh... no.

39:49.386 --> 39:50.137
I can't.

39:50.221 --> 39:53.265
I've got to chase
my dreams, too.

39:57.228 --> 39:58.979
So when are you gonna
go back home?

39:59.063 --> 40:02.316
They asked for me to be out of
the dorm by the end of the week.

40:02.399 --> 40:05.027
(sniffles)

40:06.070 --> 40:08.239
I'm gonna miss you, Donna.

40:10.324 --> 40:11.534
I'm gonna miss you, too.

40:14.078 --> 40:15.996
This is the part
that I'm not really sure

40:16.080 --> 40:17.123
what we're supposed to do.

40:17.206 --> 40:18.207
(chuckles)

40:20.876 --> 40:23.838
It's over; I guess this is
where we say good-bye.

40:23.921 --> 40:26.715
No.

40:26.799 --> 40:29.844
It's just the beginning.

40:29.927 --> 40:30.845
For both of us.

40:30.928 --> 40:32.596
(chuckles)

